From Chuck Shotton Subject Re Interesting DC X cost anecdote In article Allen Sherzer wrote A staffer just told me an interesting story about DC An Air Force costing team just looked at the DC X now called the DC BTW and gave an estimate on how much it would cost the Air Force to build It cost SDIO to build and it would cost the USAF million or four and a half times as I'd be willing to bet that a majority of the cost difference could be accounted for by the AF's requirement for superfluous documentation or huge requirements and design reviews travel expenses flying personnel around to meetings and over specifying the I doubt that the actual fabrication cost in materials and labor would be very different from SDIO's Of course this is my cynical opinion based on years of watching the government procurement process try to cover up a lack of creativity and innovation with reams of